From 30abc0f980778976840a80436d746fd445fd3e26 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: baur <baurzhansahariev@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 4 Aug 2025 15:59:49 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Avoid OOM happening on transport layer when streaming
 DistributedResultRequest

This is an alternative to https://github.com/crate/crate/pull/14114

We can't rely on PageBucketReciever's accounting, sometimes it can be too late as we can get an OOM when reading DistributedResultRequest
(in particular, reading it's StreamBucket rows field)

No change entry as we already have one in https://github.com/crate/crate/pull/18256 which is about writes and this change is about reads
but scenario is the same: aggregations under high memory pressure.
